<br>
Look around. Go on; look at those around you. See the Trolls and Frogloks drinking ale together in the corner. Note well the Koada'Dal priest nipping the neck of his Teir'Dal priestess. Eye the followers of Bertoxxulous chatting quaintly with the warriors of Tunare.<br>
<br>
Now, open your eyes and truly see. Feel the fear inside them all. Visualize the betrayal, the self-loathing, the deception, and the failure of ethics that causes all of these weaklings to betray themselves for the sake of their own power.<br>
<br>
Oh, yes, children, all here is a game, a game of power, which in the end has no rules. And why is this? Because there are really two worlds -- one material, and one spiritual. All you who touch the latter know of what I speak. The world was split long ago by the beings of power some of you might call the &quot;Pantheon,&quot; because they couldn't stand to remain in the presence of their worthless, evil creations who couldn't hold to their own paths, much less the paths set out for them from above.<br>
<br>
Shunned, the demons -- oh, aye, which we all are -- sought power over each other and over creation itself. Why? Because they're filled with hatred. For what? For their banishment from the pure unadulterated truth of the spiritual. And it's this hatred that's created the wars of our fathers, the sins of our daughters, and the deaths of our sons.<br>
<br>
I don't propose peace. I don't propose war. Both are tools of the evil stench that infests the material. No, I propose an end to everything -- not out of hate, nor righteous indignation, but out of love. I love Norrath -- I love you all -- so much because you hate yourselves. And as a loving one oft must take the hardest path to save those she loves, it is by my hand that I will see this material plane overthrown, broken, and destroyed. <br>
<br>
Death and the perfect love of annihilation await us all. I hear even now that the &quot;gods&quot; plan to wipe their twisted creation away with the purity of their purpose. While I hold no faith in any &quot;god,&quot; I appreciate that these entities know enough to cast down their inherently flawed creation.<br>
<br>
Do I hold myself above any of you? No, I don't. I, like you, am a creation of this wicked place. I, like you, am a force of evil. But I have seen the truth, and by my hand death will be brought into this world to purify it.<br>
<br>
I am Hakaisya -- the Destroyer. As in the Destroyer of Worlds. Fight against me if you will. Join me if you see the truth of my cause. Some of you will join me inadvertently in your pursuit of power; while I pity you and your misguided beliefs, every time you slay, you strengthen my cause.<br>
<br>
In the end, I, and those who stand with me, will watch the end, as the stars fade into eternal darkness, and we will be laughing as annihilation embraces us as well.<br>
<br>
