<br>
Then, his nice, quiet time in the tavern was shatterd. His steel grey eyes, locked onto the half elven woman as she spoke. A deep sigh escaped his lips as she started to spout more inane drible. As the woman finaly goes silent and steps back, Zaith rests his arm on the hilt of Tranquility, his eyes locking into hers*<br>
<br>
So, instead of preaching war or peace, you are preaching total destuction? <br>
<br>
*Zaith smirks softly*<br>
<br>
Lady...Hakaisya , was it? The Destroyer. <br>
<br>
It matters not how strong your faith in the destruction of Norrath may be, it wont happen. You are so full of fire, vigor and rage for your cause. This world is the way it is because there are those who do not care for what thier Gods teach or thier forfathers taught. The Gods make no effort to come and set us straight. Innoruuk cares not if his darkest sons and daughters have thier way with followers of Tunare. Cazic Thule does not come forth and smite us down because the Iksar marry those who destroyed thier lands. <br>
<br>
No one, mortal or God, care for what occurs on this world. <br>
<br>
*Zaith points a gauntleted finger at the woman*<br>
<br>
You claim to love us. And because of that love, you shall see us all destroyed. Such a flawed thought. You love no one here. Mayhap that is why you seek the destruction of the world. You hate everyone. For those who love, do not wish total and complete annihilation for those they claim to love. Only those who hate would seek desctrution. <br>
<br>
*Zaith takes a long drink from his ale and glances over her armor*<br>
<br>
Your colors already fit the Crimson Tear. Mayhap you should go and join Rebelle and his ilk in the Lust. They seek a grand war, mayhap you could try and destroy us all that way..<br>
<br>
